I recently forked the repository to do the work to allow theories to run discretely (i.e. one entry in the test report per combination of parameters).  Under this approach I definitely want the test marked ignored if the assumptions failed.

What I really don&#39;t like is how do you know when an assumption fails the way the theory is implemented now?  How many of the data point combinations got skipped?  Why?  That&#39;s all very useful information.


